1
00:01:37,860 --> 00:01:41,020
[The Epoch of Miyu]

2
00:01:41,090 --> 00:01:43,960
[Episode 33]

3
00:01:52,729 --> 00:01:55,789
I want you to be personally
responsible for my company.

4
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:57,380
Stop it.

5
00:01:59,830 --> 00:02:01,480
This is your first large order

6
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:02,880
in the Sales Department.

7
00:02:03,090 --> 00:02:04,150
Congratulations.

8
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:10,039
[Hotel Sales Report]

9
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:11,310
[Statement of Expenditures]

10
00:02:24,190 --> 00:02:25,310
This is

11
00:02:25,890 --> 00:02:27,870
an annual exam-taker dividend.

12
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:29,550
Ji Feng

13
00:02:29,570 --> 00:02:31,420
could only get it once.

14
00:02:32,410 --> 00:02:33,850
Mr. Wei, don't worry.

15
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,840
What about the boat pastries

16
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,800
and the Chinese restaurant?

17
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,800
Are these all dividends?

18
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,829
The profit is 10% now,

19
00:02:47,450 --> 00:02:49,579
and it's heading for 20% next quarter.

20
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,470
Don't forget our agreement with Kuanli.

21
00:02:51,470 --> 00:02:53,280
It requires 30%.

22
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:55,440
Tell me what to do!

23
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:03,640
We can look down on our opponents,

24
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:04,900
but in action,

25
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,750
we must always go all out.

26
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:07,710
Mr. Qian.

27
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:09,000
Yes.

28
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,780
Please rest assured, Mr. Wei.

29
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:15,750
I promise.

30
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:17,630
Ji Feng

31
00:03:17,870 --> 00:03:19,750
will only be happy for a moment.

32
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:20,630
Later,

33
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:22,480
I'll teach him a lesson.

34
00:03:24,630 --> 00:03:25,240
Okay.

35
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,000
I'll wait and see.

36
00:03:28,050 --> 00:03:33,800
[Art Talk]

37
00:03:28,890 --> 00:03:29,840
I'm almost done with this.

38
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,800
All right. Come over later

39
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:31,960
and help me take down the bottom.

40
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:32,360
Okay.

41
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,680
It's so tight.

42
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:36,690
[Curator: GIULIA]

43
00:03:36,079 --> 00:03:36,870
Okay.

44
00:03:37,430 --> 00:03:39,030
All right, that's it for now.

45
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:47,930
Hello.

46
00:03:47,970 --> 00:03:49,800
I thought this forum was on Friday.

47
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,280
Why are you taking it down now?

48
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,400
It's canceled.

49
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:53,710
That's impossible.

50
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:55,910
My colleagues are in charge of this event.

51
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:57,520
They were having a meeting
about it yesterday.

52
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:59,150
Well, we received a notice from leaders

53
00:03:59,150 --> 00:04:00,280
that it's canceled.

54
00:04:17,430 --> 00:04:18,360
You're all here.

55
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,660
Don't you need to go out for business?

56
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:22,160
Don't mention it.

57
00:04:22,060 --> 00:04:25,240
[Purong Hotel]

58
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:25,840
I don't know what happened to
Mr. Qian lately.

59
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:28,390
He rejected proposals
like rejecting blind dates.

60
00:04:28,390 --> 00:04:29,680
This one needed improvement,

61
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,140
and that one got rejected.

62
00:04:31,570 --> 00:04:33,030
There's no work left to do.

63
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,770
Having work isn't much better.

64
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,070
I managed to get

65
00:04:36,070 --> 00:04:37,390
a deal from a high-end tour group.

66
00:04:37,390 --> 00:04:38,630
Things were going well,

67
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:39,390
but right before signing the agreement,

68
00:04:39,390 --> 00:04:41,120
Mr. Qian suddenly changed his mind.

69
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:41,980
I asked around,

70
00:04:42,159 --> 00:04:43,360
and guess what?

71
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:44,720
Do we even need to guess?

72
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,120
They went to Kuanli.

73
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,680
It's not just you.

74
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:49,870
Recently, several colleagues' orders

75
00:04:49,870 --> 00:04:52,040
were inexplicably snatched by Kuanli.

76
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,159
Believe it or not,

77
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,840
the Q4 performance

78
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:58,070
will be worse than those in the rainy
and typhoon seasons.

79
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:02,240
Aren't we going to think of a solution?

80
00:05:03,270 --> 00:05:04,530
What can we do?

81
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:06,210
The bosses are slacking off.

82
00:05:06,210 --> 00:05:07,510
We are just nobody.

83
00:05:07,510 --> 00:05:09,110
Why should we worry about it?

84
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:12,070
I heard

85
00:05:12,070 --> 00:05:15,060
Mr. Qian and Mr. Ji are
fighting against each other.

86
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:17,440
He is obviously embarrassing Mr. Ji.

87
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:20,470
The one-year VAM agreement is almost up.

88
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:23,550
Mr. Ji is under a lot of pressure.

89
00:05:24,650 --> 00:05:25,520
Let's go.

90
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,920
The deadline for the VAM agreement
is approaching.

91
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:36,650
Is the hotel doing well lately?

92
00:05:37,310 --> 00:05:38,830
It's fine. Don't worry.

93
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:40,600
Why do you suddenly ask?

94
00:05:41,390 --> 00:05:42,510
I heard that Qian Xun has been

95
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:44,630
obstructing the Sales
Department's orders lately.

96
00:05:44,630 --> 00:05:46,159
Is there anything I can do to help you?

97
00:05:46,159 --> 00:05:47,600
You're dealing with

98
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,159
Qian Xun and Lu Zhenzhen
in the Sales Department.

99
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:50,820
Actually, you're helping me.

100
00:05:53,950 --> 00:05:56,510
What? Don't you believe in your boyfriend?

101
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:02,280
All right, don't worry too much.

102
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,690
Go on up.

103
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,560
Be careful.

104
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:11,800
Miyu.

105
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:14,040
I heard you're no longer
in the Front Office.

106
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,100
So I came to see you.

107
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:16,430
Want to eat together?

108
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:19,250
Okay, we can talk while having dinner.

109
00:06:20,430 --> 00:06:22,800
Two wonton noodles, please.

110
00:06:23,830 --> 00:06:24,310
Okay.

111
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:32,420
Have I gotten tanned

112
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,070
from running field errands?

113
00:06:34,070 --> 00:06:34,830
No.

114
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,720
You're not holding a walkie-talkie

115
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,360
or wearing a uniform anymore.

116
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,830
It's so good

117
00:06:40,830 --> 00:06:41,690
to be yourself.

118
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,720
I remember the first time I met you,

119
00:06:45,510 --> 00:06:48,040
you were like a frightened bird,

120
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:49,510
trying desperately to please

121
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:50,720
everyone around you.

122
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:52,510
But after that, every time I saw you,

123
00:06:52,510 --> 00:06:54,970
I found you a little different
from the last,

124
00:06:55,510 --> 00:06:57,060
more confident,

125
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,750
happier,

126
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,680
bolder,

127
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:02,510
and more…

128
00:07:02,950 --> 00:07:05,350
Anyway, you're getting better and better.

129
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,920
You seem to enjoy your work.

130
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,720
I truly feel

131
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:12,330
this can be my lifelong stage.

132
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,800
There is a lot of scheming

133
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,920
and deception,

134
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:16,630
but

135
00:07:16,950 --> 00:07:18,480
these underhanded tricks

136
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,610
are not the core of the hotel industry.

137
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:23,100
The true spirit of the hotel industry

138
00:07:23,430 --> 00:07:24,850
is always

139
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:26,690
making guests feel at home,

140
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,800
which is the best metaphor for life.

141
00:07:32,270 --> 00:07:33,000
Miyu,

142
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:34,120
I really envy you

143
00:07:34,390 --> 00:07:36,320
for finding your own stage in life.

144
00:07:41,159 --> 00:07:43,360
Is something on your mind, Mr. Tan?

145
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,360
No, nothing.

146
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,960
Just a spontaneous thought.

147
00:07:58,130 --> 00:08:01,850
[Tan Jizhou]

148
00:08:04,170 --> 00:08:06,450
[Tan Jizhou]

149
00:08:08,460 --> 00:08:09,310
[Revealing exhibition of
Golden Times]

150
00:08:09,330 --> 00:08:10,010
[of independent curator
Tan Jizhou delays infinitely]

151
00:08:10,030 --> 00:08:11,080
[Tan Jizhou's exhibition hall is pending]

152
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,360
[Independent curator Tan Jizhou's
divorce gossip]

153
00:08:17,570 --> 00:08:19,930
[Tan Jizhou's exhibition is
in trouble with uncertain future]

154
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:21,100
[Today, a piece of pitiful news is]

155
00:08:21,130 --> 00:08:22,520
[spreading on various platforms.]

156
00:08:24,610 --> 00:08:25,710
[It is reported that
the exhibition hall is]

157
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:26,950
[still pending. This has brought
a lot of uncertainties]

158
00:08:26,970 --> 00:08:28,240
[to the exhibition plan]

159
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,580
Mr. Tan.

160
00:08:44,910 --> 00:08:45,390
Please.

161
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:45,840
Okay.

162
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:52,900
I'm surprised you asked me out.

163
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:57,590
-I wish I hadn’t taken up much time.
-Of course not.

164
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,360
What's up?

165
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:01,840
I heard you were going to
hold an art exhibition.

166
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:04,840
So I searched for the news online

167
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,270
and found out

168
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:08,110
your exhibition

169
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:09,550
isn't going well.

170
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:11,360
Thank you

171
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:13,090
for worrying about my affairs.

172
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:14,960
The situation is

173
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,030
a bit complicated.

174
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:18,150
In short,

175
00:09:18,150 --> 00:09:20,080
I'm not satisfied with

176
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,580
the hotel in Hong Kong.

177
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:24,120
Could you tell me why?

178
00:09:24,180 --> 00:09:25,190
Of course.

179
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,010
The thing is,

180
00:09:27,270 --> 00:09:29,490
they couldn't provide the space I want.

181
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:30,960
But my core team

182
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,200
wanted me to compromise

183
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:34,800
because they've already
paid a hefty deposit.

184
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:39,150
What kind of space do you want?

185
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:45,100
Flowing, non-standardized

186
00:09:45,130 --> 00:09:46,800
and time-honored.

187
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:49,030
The theme of my curation this time
is called

188
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:49,790
"Time",

189
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:50,910
so I really

190
00:09:50,910 --> 00:09:52,480
want to present a feeling of

191
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,580
time flowing.

192
00:09:53,610 --> 00:09:54,840
But right now, this venue

193
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,780
is as boring as a matchbox.

194
00:09:56,810 --> 00:09:58,140
Actually, I just want to

195
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,710
break its boxy feel

196
00:09:59,750 --> 00:10:01,390
and add some dynamic installations.

197
00:10:01,390 --> 00:10:02,150
But I don't know why

198
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:04,150
everyone thinks I'm dreaming.

199
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,650
By everyone, you mean?

200
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:10,000
The venue manager,

201
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,030
my core team,

202
00:10:11,030 --> 00:10:12,120
and my CFO.

203
00:10:13,510 --> 00:10:14,550
Miss Lin Nanxin.

204
00:10:18,820 --> 00:10:20,620
You've really read a lot of news.

205
00:10:22,390 --> 00:10:23,000
Yes.

206
00:10:23,910 --> 00:10:25,440
She is my ex-wife.

207
00:10:26,060 --> 00:10:27,150
Actually, in our careers,

208
00:10:27,150 --> 00:10:28,870
we are so compatible

209
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:31,390
that we had to break up our family

210
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:32,790
and devote all our energy to

211
00:10:32,790 --> 00:10:34,520
building our curatorial team.

212
00:10:35,550 --> 00:10:38,350
But this time she also thought
I'm messing around.

213
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:40,180
I don't have any choices.

214
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:44,790
What if we change the approach?

215
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:46,370
What do you mean?

216
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,910
Do you have time

217
00:10:48,970 --> 00:10:50,670
to listen to my idea?

218
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:51,480
Of course.

219
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:55,450
[Jixuan Hall] [Bilan Hall]

220
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:56,510
Purong has such a place?

221
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:58,720
Your theme is time,

222
00:10:58,740 --> 00:11:00,200
so I thought of this place.

223
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,600
Purong Hotel records

224
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:04,600
the memories of several generations.

225
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:07,510
Whether in terms of architectural style
or cultural heritage,

226
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:09,510
it quite matches

227
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:11,710
the sense of accumulated time you want.

228
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:12,320
Yes.

229
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:15,440
Indeed, the venues in Hong Kong

230
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:16,360
are too modern

231
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,620
and too standardized.

232
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,000
In this way,

233
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:19,750
Purong's style

234
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:21,750
really fits my idea.

235
00:11:22,630 --> 00:11:24,690
But this space…

236
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:26,240
These two

237
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:28,040
are our two small banquet halls.

238
00:11:28,330 --> 00:11:30,050
They are not square,

239
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:32,020
[Jixuan Hall] [Bilan Hall]

240
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:32,240
so they are not used frequently.

241
00:11:32,510 --> 00:11:33,510
But I think

242
00:11:33,510 --> 00:11:35,840
its irregular shape

243
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:38,240
provides more wall space.

244
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:38,870
In this regard,

245
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:41,400
it's more beneficial
for the art exhibition.

246
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:44,000
This time, we can connect the two spaces.

247
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,000
You can use

248
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,150
the entire space freely.

249
00:11:47,390 --> 00:11:49,720
In the middle, we can connect

250
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,390
the two halls with a corridor.

251
00:11:49,770 --> 00:11:51,260
[Jixuan Hall] [Bilan Hall]

252
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,720
We can put some video

253
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:54,440
installations inside

254
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:57,510
to create a feeling of flowing time,

255
00:11:57,510 --> 00:12:00,270
allowing the audience
to pass through this time tunnel

256
00:12:00,270 --> 00:12:01,270
to your artistic world.

257
00:12:01,270 --> 00:12:02,510
Sorry to interrupt.

258
00:12:04,510 --> 00:12:05,390
If...

259
00:12:05,390 --> 00:12:06,870
I mean, if I hold the exhibition...

260
00:12:06,870 --> 00:12:08,440
Purong Hotel is definitely perfect for it.

261
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,320
Trust me.

262
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:12,600
If you're willing to consider this space,

263
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,240
I can take you to the field.

264
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:15,840
You can do whatever you want.

265
00:12:16,230 --> 00:12:17,390
Really?

266
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:19,240
Because this is so far

267
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:20,960
the most ideal venue I've ever seen.

268
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:23,200
But for a five-star hotel like Purong,

269
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:25,630
I don't think turning a banquet hall
into an art exhibition

270
00:12:25,630 --> 00:12:27,320
serves your interests.

271
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,600
Actually, we need

272
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,080
this art exhibition more than you think.

273
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:32,200
So I will do my best to fight for it.

274
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,240
Thank you. Thank you.

275
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:34,840
Thank you.

276
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:35,480
Mr. Tan.

277
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:36,840
Mr. Tan.

278
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:38,030
I'm sorry.

279
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,360
I got too excited.

280
00:12:39,380 --> 00:12:40,260
My apologies.

281
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,920
Wish us a happy cooperation.

282
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:47,080
Wish us a happy cooperation.

283
00:12:48,940 --> 00:12:49,910
I disagree.

284
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,670
You want to

285
00:12:51,670 --> 00:12:53,440
enhance the hotel's influence

286
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,300
by holding crossover art events.

287
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:56,760
The idea is right.

288
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:58,670
But you want to connect

289
00:12:58,670 --> 00:13:00,540
two underutilized banquet halls

290
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:02,330
to host an art exhibition.

291
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:03,840
What happens after the exhibition?

292
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:04,980
[Purong Hotel]

293
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,640
How do you plan to use this space?

294
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:06,670
These two banquet halls

295
00:13:06,670 --> 00:13:08,440
have a poor layout

296
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,080
and a low utilization rate

297
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,670
due to the load-bearing walls.

298
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:13,510
If we connect them now,

299
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:15,360
it will look like a small art gallery.

300
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,750
I think we can turn it into

301
00:13:16,750 --> 00:13:18,600
an exclusive art space for Purong Hotel.

302
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,600
You mean

303
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,270
making

304
00:13:21,790 --> 00:13:22,750
these two banquet halls

305
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:24,600
into a permanent art gallery?

306
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,200
Purong Hotel has a long history

307
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:28,000
and is known for its high-end taste.

308
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,440
Many clients choose us

309
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:31,480
for our cultural heritage.

310
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:34,320
Whether we host regular art exhibitions

311
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:35,440
or use this space

312
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:37,600
to display our hotel's

313
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:38,630
cultural history,

314
00:13:38,630 --> 00:13:40,000
it's in the hotel's best interest.

315
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,910
In the hotel's interest?

316
00:13:41,910 --> 00:13:43,960
Is your idea supported by data?

317
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,870
We need solid data

318
00:13:46,870 --> 00:13:48,510
and a risk assessment

319
00:13:48,510 --> 00:13:49,960
to determine if a project is profitable.

320
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:50,960
Let's not look too far ahead.

321
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:52,450
Just discuss the exhibition itself.

322
00:13:52,450 --> 00:13:53,510
As for the venue setup,

323
00:13:52,490 --> 00:13:54,060
[Purong Hotel]

324
00:13:53,510 --> 00:13:54,750
the security of the exhibits,

325
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,030
and the services during the exhibition,

326
00:13:56,030 --> 00:13:58,240
how much manpower
and resources are needed?

327
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:00,840
Are you confident in recouping costs?

328
00:14:01,030 --> 00:14:02,120
Have you evaluated the value of

329
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,510
the exhibition itself?

330
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:04,720
Is it worth

331
00:14:04,910 --> 00:14:06,200
dedicating

332
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:07,480
two banquet halls at once?

333
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:08,720
I will do detailed research

334
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,720
on all of that.

335
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:12,240
But there are successful cases of

336
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,550
hotels using art exhibitions

337
00:14:13,550 --> 00:14:16,070
to enhance their influence.

338
00:14:16,070 --> 00:14:17,790
I think we can give it a try

339
00:14:17,790 --> 00:14:19,030
and work to minimize the risks,

340
00:14:19,030 --> 00:14:20,670
instead of rejecting it

341
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:21,630
without even trying.

342
00:14:21,630 --> 00:14:24,200
Purong Hotel is at a critical moment now.

343
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:25,840
It's not a proper time for
trial and error.

344
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,670
Because it's a critical moment for us,

345
00:14:27,670 --> 00:14:29,480
we should make a bold breakthrough.

346
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,840
That's what you taught me.

347
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:31,950
This is not a breakthrough,

348
00:14:31,950 --> 00:14:33,350
but a reckless movement.

349
00:14:34,510 --> 00:14:35,790
I thought you would support me.

350
00:14:35,790 --> 00:14:37,030
Do you want me to

351
00:14:37,060 --> 00:14:38,910
support you unconditionally

352
00:14:38,910 --> 00:14:40,080
even if knowing your proposal
is highly risky?

353
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,200
What do you mean?

354
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,240
I'm talking about work.

355
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:43,960
Me too.

356
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:58,240
I want to support you.

357
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,590
But the internal strife is too fierce.

358
00:15:01,610 --> 00:15:03,290
I don't want you to be the target.

359
00:15:03,290 --> 00:15:05,470
What's your point of saying that,

360
00:15:05,490 --> 00:15:06,970
boss or boyfriend?

361
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:13,320
Am I vulnerable in your eyes?

362
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,120
I will prove that

363
00:15:17,140 --> 00:15:19,200
the art exhibition is worth holding.

364
00:15:26,620 --> 00:15:29,270
[Purong Hotel Staff Apartment]

365
00:15:29,370 --> 00:15:33,850
[Image-type Curation Cases]

366
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:44,500
[Missed Calls from Ji Feng]

367
00:15:46,170 --> 00:15:48,760
[Ji Feng]

368
00:15:49,060 --> 00:15:50,100
[I'm almost at the cinema.]

369
00:15:50,130 --> 00:15:51,300
[Where are you?]

370
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,610
[Will you come?]

371
00:16:02,140 --> 00:16:04,890
[Sorry. I forgot that we had arranged to
go to the cinema today.]

372
00:16:04,890 --> 00:16:06,700
[Sorry. I forgot that we had arranged to
go to the cinema today.]

373
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,360
[There's a later show.]

374
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:11,050
[Ji Feng]

375
00:16:09,270 --> 00:16:10,330
[Want to watch it?]

376
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:16,200
[It's too late. Let's do it another day.]

377
00:16:14,510 --> 00:16:15,590
[Xu Miyu]

378
00:16:16,670 --> 00:16:17,390
[Okay.]

379
00:16:17,060 --> 00:16:19,830
[Ji Feng]

380
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:29,270
[Rest early. Good night.]

381
00:16:28,610 --> 00:16:31,580
[Xu Miyu]

382
00:16:35,010 --> 00:16:39,670
[Ji Feng]

383
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:50,630
[Rest early. Good night.]

384
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,630
A disagreement at work during the day

385
00:16:55,780 --> 00:16:57,600
will unknowingly

386
00:16:57,630 --> 00:16:59,290
kill the romance of the night.

387
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:01,170
Gradually,

388
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:03,600
we stop trying to distinguish

389
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,829
between love and working together.

390
00:17:06,349 --> 00:17:07,589
Our love

391
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:09,940
is mixed with more and more rationality.

392
00:17:18,550 --> 00:17:19,680
What are you doing?

393
00:17:20,099 --> 00:17:21,520
Spacing out?

394
00:17:21,829 --> 00:17:22,640
No.

395
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,329
I slept late last night.

396
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:28,610
Well,

397
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,110
Yuntian Group from New Zealand

398
00:17:31,310 --> 00:17:33,000
is coming to China for bidding.

399
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,000
I heard they're coming to Shanghai.

400
00:17:35,110 --> 00:17:36,590
Yuntian Group?

401
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:38,750
Are you talking about

402
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:41,260
that energy trading group in the top 50?

403
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,180
Rui, what's your opinion?

404
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:45,160
We should go all out, of course.

405
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:46,030
Just say the word,

406
00:17:46,030 --> 00:17:47,490
and I'll act immediately.

407
00:17:47,790 --> 00:17:48,270
I...

408
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:50,920
I haven't thought it through yet.

409
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:52,350
Our only advantage right now is that

410
00:17:52,350 --> 00:17:54,280
we got the information in advance.

411
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:56,720
I guess we'll be caught up soon.

412
00:17:57,270 --> 00:17:58,240
Anyway,

413
00:17:58,240 --> 00:17:59,510
we should hold an internal meeting to

414
00:17:59,510 --> 00:18:01,270
discuss the plan first.

415
00:18:01,590 --> 00:18:03,050
Brainstorming is useful.

416
00:18:03,510 --> 00:18:04,030
Okay.

417
00:18:04,030 --> 00:18:06,240
I'll have Secretary Wu
notify the directors.

418
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:06,880
We'll hold a meeting

419
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:07,960
to sync up.

420
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:10,640
No.

421
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:13,640
It's past five.

422
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:14,590
And it's the weekend.

423
00:18:14,590 --> 00:18:15,920
Next week is fine.

424
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:19,310
Okay.

425
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:21,510
By the way,

426
00:18:21,830 --> 00:18:24,640
haven't your insomnia symptoms
eased a lot?

427
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:26,400
No.

428
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,960
It's seasonal.

429
00:18:29,350 --> 00:18:30,270
Your insomnia

430
00:18:30,590 --> 00:18:31,960
is seasonal?

431
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:34,860
I think you're trapped in love.

432
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:37,120
Having a conflict again?

433
00:18:37,210 --> 00:18:38,090
No.

434
00:18:41,070 --> 00:18:42,130
Give me your phone.

435
00:18:43,110 --> 00:18:43,790
What for?

436
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:46,640
You can't just rely on your mind to love.

437
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:48,720
You need to explain

438
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:50,110
and coax her.

439
00:18:58,740 --> 00:18:59,370
Wait.

440
00:19:07,850 --> 00:19:12,480
[Li Qiaoqi]

441
00:19:08,510 --> 00:19:11,170
[Come to my place after work.
I'll cook for you.]

442
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:12,590
[Okay.]

443
00:19:14,450 --> 00:19:14,590
[Li Qiaoqi]

444
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:15,620
[Ji Feng] [Are you free after work?]

445
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:17,770
[Ji Feng]

446
00:19:17,770 --> 00:19:18,400
[Sorry. I forgot that we had arranged to
go to the cinema today.]

447
00:19:18,430 --> 00:19:18,910
[There's another one later.
Want to watch it?]

448
00:19:18,930 --> 00:19:19,700
[It's too late. Maybe another day.]

449
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,480
[Are you free after work?]

450
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:20,340
[Okay.]

451
00:19:26,110 --> 00:19:26,910
[Sorry.]

452
00:19:27,230 --> 00:19:28,560
[I have plans tonight.]

453
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:40,130
[Xu Miyu]

454
00:19:40,210 --> 00:19:43,360
[Sorry, I have plans tonight.]

455
00:19:50,310 --> 00:19:51,270
I'm off work.

456
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:52,770
Have a good weekend.

457
00:19:57,990 --> 00:20:00,110
I will treat you to a big meal.

458
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:00,960
Come with me.

459
00:20:02,350 --> 00:20:03,000
Let's go.

460
00:20:15,350 --> 00:20:16,920
Six kinds of cold dishes
with aged vinegar.

461
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:18,850
Try it. It's their signature dish.

462
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:22,920
Don't just drink. Eat something.

463
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:34,170
Why is it so sour?

464
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:37,400
It's fine.

465
00:20:38,830 --> 00:20:40,230
Maybe your mouth is sour.

466
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:45,830
We're eating.

467
00:20:46,070 --> 00:20:47,400
What are you hinting at?

468
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,350
Nothing.

469
00:20:49,310 --> 00:20:50,310
Tell me.

470
00:20:50,670 --> 00:20:52,840
What happened between you and Xu Miyu?

471
00:20:54,460 --> 00:20:55,330
She and I

472
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:57,770
had a disagreement at work.

473
00:20:57,940 --> 00:20:59,870
I don't know why she

474
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:01,960
insisted on holding
Tan Jizhou's art exhibition

475
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,270
at Purong Hotel.

476
00:21:04,090 --> 00:21:05,250
Isn't that great?

477
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:07,410
Qian Xun has been

478
00:21:07,430 --> 00:21:09,110
giving you a hard time lately.

479
00:21:09,290 --> 00:21:11,310
It's a good chance to take him down a peg.

480
00:21:11,310 --> 00:21:12,550
It's not that simple.

481
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:14,850
She is in the Sales Department now.

482
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,750
She can't be as naive as before.

483
00:21:17,570 --> 00:21:18,570
Stop right there.

484
00:21:19,170 --> 00:21:20,640
Xu Miyu is not

485
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:22,240
a naive girl.

486
00:21:22,510 --> 00:21:24,900
I think you're overcomplicating things.

487
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:27,570
Actually, no.

488
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:32,030
You're probably oversimplifying it.

489
00:21:33,150 --> 00:21:35,430
You're just being petty.

490
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:37,470
Me?

491
00:21:37,760 --> 00:21:38,820
I'm petty?

492
00:21:39,990 --> 00:21:42,320
You might call the shots at work,

493
00:21:42,340 --> 00:21:44,670
but emotionally, you're inexperienced.

494
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:47,990
You've worked abroad
for so many years.

495
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:52,310
Haven't you handled weirder projects

496
00:21:52,310 --> 00:21:54,110
than hosting an art exhibition?

497
00:21:55,310 --> 00:21:56,310
So,

498
00:21:56,950 --> 00:21:58,430
think it through.

499
00:21:58,450 --> 00:22:01,250
Are you worried about
the risk of holding the art exhibition

500
00:22:01,250 --> 00:22:04,180
or the person
who is going to hold the art exhibition?

501
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:14,550
Are you angry that Mr. Ji

502
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:15,960
rejected your proposal

503
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,550
or that your boyfriend didn't

504
00:22:17,550 --> 00:22:18,750
support your career?

505
00:22:19,890 --> 00:22:20,930
I don't know.

506
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Maybe both.

507
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:27,270
Let me analyze it for you.

508
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:31,160
Ji Feng is a devil in the workplace.

509
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:33,110
You know it clearly, right?

510
00:22:35,750 --> 00:22:39,310
After work, you two are dating.

511
00:22:39,750 --> 00:22:42,070
Using date time to talk about work

512
00:22:42,070 --> 00:22:44,000
is highly not recommended.

513
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:45,480
Agree?

514
00:22:49,140 --> 00:22:51,660
So, whether it's the former or the latter,

515
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:53,340
there's no need to be unhappy.

516
00:22:54,310 --> 00:22:55,920
You're right.

517
00:22:56,310 --> 00:22:57,590
But

518
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,830
we are human beings,

519
00:22:59,830 --> 00:23:01,640
not two machines.

520
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:04,830
There is no switch
to instantly change modes.

521
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:06,400
I was arguing with him

522
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:08,200
in the office during the day.

523
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,830
When we go on a date at night,

524
00:23:10,830 --> 00:23:12,030
how can I smile at him?

525
00:23:14,110 --> 00:23:17,110
Miyu, I think you should relax.

526
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:20,240
No matter how many relationships you have,

527
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:22,110
the process of
getting along with each other

528
00:23:22,110 --> 00:23:24,110
matters the most.

529
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:26,200
Just like us.

530
00:23:26,590 --> 00:23:29,250
We've known each other
for almost thirty years.

531
00:23:29,350 --> 00:23:30,920
We were neighbors,

532
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:32,280
best friends,

533
00:23:32,470 --> 00:23:33,550
classmates,

534
00:23:33,550 --> 00:23:34,790
and now colleagues.

535
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,830
We almost cut ties

536
00:23:36,830 --> 00:23:38,270
because of a jerk.

537
00:23:38,590 --> 00:23:39,720
But we made up

538
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:40,580
after arguing.

539
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:41,960
We will always be each other’s

540
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:43,400
most important partner.

541
00:23:45,830 --> 00:23:46,640
You are right.

542
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:50,720
But objectively speaking,

543
00:23:50,960 --> 00:23:53,400
I completely understand your frustration.

544
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:54,640
Mr. Ji

545
00:23:54,790 --> 00:23:56,500
seems to be good at everything,

546
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:57,960
but his tongue

547
00:23:57,960 --> 00:23:59,550
is really annoying.

548
00:24:00,590 --> 00:24:01,960
I support you in training him.

549
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:04,690
Start with the proposal
for this art exhibition.

550
00:24:04,790 --> 00:24:07,000
Let him know your vision and ability

551
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:08,810
are not inferior to his at all.

552
00:24:10,590 --> 00:24:11,350
Yes!

553
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,600
You can do it, Xu Miyu.

554
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:17,990
[Purong Hotel Staff Apartment]

555
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:21,880
A successful art exhibition

556
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:24,730
is the resonance of the curator's
and the creator's souls.

557
00:24:24,730 --> 00:24:25,880
It is the dome and high walls

558
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:28,340
blending perfectly with colors and shapes.

559
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:29,720
A good curator

560
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:31,130
needs to have the courage and insight

561
00:24:31,130 --> 00:24:33,810
to break and reconstruct art.

562
00:24:31,610 --> 00:24:32,120
[Hidden Island Hotel Group:
Art ExhibitionRealm]

563
00:24:32,150 --> 00:24:32,910
[Harmony of Art and Nature]

564
00:24:33,090 --> 00:24:34,910
[Art Space:Immersive Experience
of Nature and Art]

565
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,480
Outside the world of works,

566
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:36,440
he builds another artistic world

567
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:39,000
with greater inclusivity.

568
00:24:54,780 --> 00:24:55,520
[Transformation sign of banquet halls
of Purong Hotel]

569
00:24:56,270 --> 00:24:57,900
[Banquet Hall] [Room]

570
00:25:06,540 --> 00:25:07,340
I'm sorry.

571
00:25:07,790 --> 00:25:09,850
I came to have a look
out of curiosity.

572
00:25:22,030 --> 00:25:24,030
I have investigated the risks,

573
00:25:24,030 --> 00:25:26,070
which are elaborated on page three.

