858
00:37:19,110 --> 00:37:20,590
This one is from the later period.

859
00:37:20,590 --> 00:37:22,480
This was with a friend.

860
00:37:22,710 --> 00:37:24,670
These works are so bold.

861
00:37:25,510 --> 00:37:26,150
Yes.

862
00:37:26,670 --> 00:37:28,750
This is the beginning of the story.

863
00:37:29,630 --> 00:37:31,920
It's like a child who just
came into this world,

864
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:33,090
full of curiosity about everything,

865
00:37:33,090 --> 00:37:34,190
and charging recklessly.

866
00:37:34,190 --> 00:37:35,440
But if you look closely,

867
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:36,760
you'll find the colors and lines

868
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:38,490
are handled in such a naive way.

869
00:37:39,630 --> 00:37:41,070
As expected of Mr. Tan.

870
00:37:41,630 --> 00:37:43,630
The ingenuity is all in the details.

871
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:47,960
Actually, this is my early work.

872
00:37:48,630 --> 00:37:49,590
I'll leave it to you two.

873
00:37:49,590 --> 00:37:50,550
I'll go keep an eye on things over there.

874
00:37:50,550 --> 00:37:51,110
Okay.

875
00:37:52,190 --> 00:37:53,150
Slow down a bit.

876
00:37:56,710 --> 00:37:58,710
Miyu is so careful and sharp.

877
00:37:58,710 --> 00:38:00,440
It's a pity she's not a curator.

878
00:38:02,230 --> 00:38:05,560
Are you trying to poach my staff
right in front of me, Mr. Tan?

879
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,150
You're too sensitive, Mr. Ji.

880
00:38:07,150 --> 00:38:08,190
I dare not.

881
00:38:09,150 --> 00:38:09,840
Mr. Ji,

882
00:38:10,190 --> 00:38:12,070
What do you think of our exhibition?

883
00:38:12,070 --> 00:38:14,110
Is it worthy of Purong's banquet hall?

884
00:38:14,110 --> 00:38:15,110
You are too polite.

885
00:38:15,110 --> 00:38:16,630
Mr. Tan's art exhibition

886
00:38:16,630 --> 00:38:18,440
adds so much color

887
00:38:18,440 --> 00:38:20,280
to our hotel's banquet halls.

888
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:21,190
You flatter me.

889
00:38:21,630 --> 00:38:24,400
However, I noticed the introduction
to each artwork

890
00:38:24,400 --> 00:38:26,670
uses a QR code.

891
00:38:25,210 --> 00:38:27,380
[Scan and check the profile of Tan Jizhou]

892
00:38:26,670 --> 00:38:27,960
But since our hotel

893
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:29,630
has quite a few

894
00:38:29,630 --> 00:38:30,920
elderly guests,

895
00:38:31,190 --> 00:38:32,360
wouldn't this be

896
00:38:32,360 --> 00:38:33,590
unfriendly to them?

897
00:38:35,590 --> 00:38:37,800
I didn't think this through.

898
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:39,720
But there's something
you don't know, Mr. Ji.

899
00:38:39,720 --> 00:38:42,030
Large blocks of text

900
00:38:42,030 --> 00:38:43,190
would be too complicated.

901
00:38:43,190 --> 00:38:44,590
For our exhibition,

902
00:38:44,610 --> 00:38:46,400
it would create a visual burden.

903
00:38:46,400 --> 00:38:47,840
The loss would outweigh the gain.

904
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:49,570
Why don't we provide brochures

905
00:38:49,630 --> 00:38:50,800
for those who need them?

906
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:51,800
What do you think?

907
00:38:53,070 --> 00:38:54,000
It makes sense.

908
00:38:55,110 --> 00:38:56,230
Anyway,

909
00:38:56,960 --> 00:38:58,890
holding this exhibition at Purong

910
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:00,850
is my best decision.

911
00:39:01,590 --> 00:39:02,970
Pleasure working with you.

912
00:39:02,970 --> 00:39:04,510
Thank you for your trust, Mr. Tan.

913
00:39:04,510 --> 00:39:05,840
With our joint efforts,

914
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:06,670
this art exhibition

915
00:39:06,670 --> 00:39:08,550
will definitely be a huge success.

916
00:39:08,550 --> 00:39:09,320
I believe so.

917
00:39:09,590 --> 00:39:10,400
Gentlemen,

918
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:11,630
the main exhibit is up on the wall.

919
00:39:11,630 --> 00:39:12,670
Would you like to go and take a look?

920
00:39:12,670 --> 00:39:13,440
Let's take a look.

921
00:39:13,440 --> 00:39:14,150
Let's go.

922
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:23,320
Is this the one to be unveiled tomorrow,

923
00:39:23,320 --> 00:39:24,480
the new work, "Time"?

924
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:25,230
Exactly.

925
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:28,190
In the past, when we talked about time,

926
00:39:28,190 --> 00:39:31,110
we always thought of the passing time.

927
00:39:31,110 --> 00:39:31,710
But

928
00:39:31,710 --> 00:39:34,230
after seeing so many works of Mr. Tan,

929
00:39:34,370 --> 00:39:35,070
I found that time

930
00:39:35,070 --> 00:39:36,800
brings all kinds of people

931
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:38,480
into our lives.

932
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:39,480
It's like each of us

933
00:39:39,480 --> 00:39:40,760
is a hotel,

934
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:43,230
spending a lifetime
welcoming and seeing others off.

935
00:39:43,230 --> 00:39:45,110
There is laughter and regret.

936
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:46,840
The most important thing

937
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:49,590
is to cherish every encounter.

938
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:52,560
I really like this explanation.

939
00:39:53,320 --> 00:39:54,110
Miyu.

940
00:39:55,190 --> 00:39:56,070
Thank you.

941
00:39:56,070 --> 00:39:57,840
Thank you for giving me

942
00:39:57,840 --> 00:39:59,450
such a wonderful possibility.

943
00:39:59,450 --> 00:40:00,640
So I hope

944
00:40:00,670 --> 00:40:03,070
you can cover it
with the curtain yourself.

945
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:04,700
I'd be honored.

946
00:40:07,150 --> 00:40:07,630
Come on.

947
00:40:07,630 --> 00:40:08,480
Thank you.

948
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:16,050
Come on. Be careful.

949
00:40:18,040 --> 00:40:18,990
Careful.

950
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:25,280
Okay, slowly.

951
00:40:27,590 --> 00:40:28,440
Okay.

952
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:33,630
Please.
